employment.description:
● Worked closely with organizational leadership, including board of directors, to strategically affect the direction of operations.
● Developed an innovative tool that enabled assessment of lab capacity and throughput, providing the framework for managing a $950,000 budget.
● Managed teams of 12 professionals focused on improving media.
● Supervised the writing of all grant applications and ensured that information was accurate prior to submission.
● Introduced a new matrix organizational plan with clear roles and responsibilities to enhance processes while ensuring quality and regulatory compliance.
● Oversees the research staff, puts forward plans and directions for needed policy research, as well as, manage and channels the resources;
● Monitored and reported budgetary discrepancies to corporate senior management to maximize reporting efficiency and finalized spending plans.
● Prepared documents, reports and presentations for executives and board members using advanced software proficiency.
● Quality assurance of all research and publications;
● Managed the data hub and index of all information that will later serve journalists and researchers in their work;
● Map CBO’s and assess their capacities. In additions to developing their capacities accordingly and highlighting their work with coordination with journalists;
● Developed training curriculum to target CBOs and provide training where needed.
● Oversee, manage and provide reports to both donors and the Board of Directors about the two main programs: Access to Justice and Access to Information.
